long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I get this crash from time to time when hitting Ctrl+N to open a new window.
Version-Release number of selected component: evince-3.22.1-1.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: evince '/home/milan/.mozilla/firefox/i0t8o9gm.default/zotero/storage/5WMEBWD5/Goodman & Hout, A Modified Regression-Type Approach.pdf' crash_function: _gtk_widget_get_toplevel executable: /usr/bin/evince global_pid: 30342 kernel: 4.8.11-300.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 _gtk_widget_get_toplevel at gtkwidgetprivate.h:381 #1 gtk_widget_get_scale_factor at gtkwidget.c:10881 #2 gtk_css_widget_node_get_style_provider at gtkcsswidgetnode.c:250 #3 gtk_css_node_get_style_provider_or_null at gtkcssnode.c:121 #4 gtk_css_node_invalidate_style_provider at gtkcssnode.c:1316 #9 _gtk_style_provider_private_changed at gtkstyleproviderprivate.c:113 #10 _gtk_style_cascade_add_provider at gtkstylecascade.c:380 #11 gtk_style_context_add_provider_for_screen at gtkstylecontext.c:718 #12 ev_window_init at ev-window.c:6724 #13 g_type_create_instance at gtype.c:1866
multiple ctrl+n didn't turn up anything here. I wonder if its more generic than evince, what's the version of gtk3 ?
GTK is 3.22.4-1. Forgot to say I have an external monitor via a docking station.
I can reproduce this systematically here: it always happens the second time I open a new window using the context menu on a hyperlink.
hmm, I can actually reproduce this (with export G_SLICE=always-malloc)
